        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 5:17PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Christoval, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Christoval.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
